1
00:01:34,795 --> 00:01:36,163
Is there something wrong with this guy?

2
00:01:36,229 --> 00:01:38,165
He has been beaten up so badly,
but he's still standing.

3
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:56,883
Are you done?

4
00:01:58,752 --> 00:02:00,153
I didn't feel anything at all.

5
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:03,323
Do you want to have a go, too?

6
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:06,526
This is for my brother!

7
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,261
You're not afraid to die?

8
00:02:24,111 --> 00:02:25,345
Darn it. Beat the girl up, too.

9
00:02:25,412 --> 00:02:26,413
Stop.

10
00:02:34,187 --> 00:02:35,188
That's enough.

11
00:02:35,255 --> 00:02:36,256
Let's go.

12
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:43,964
That's a lesson for you.

13
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:45,432
Don't be too arrogant from now on.

14
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:47,300
Jerk, just wait and see.

15
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:50,804
Daoming Si.

16
00:02:50,871 --> 00:02:52,372
Daoming Si, are you okay?

17
00:02:54,975 --> 00:02:56,510
How can I be okay?

18
00:02:58,612 --> 00:02:59,780
My hand

19
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:02,883
and my ribs are almost broken.

20
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:06,653
Stupid fool!

21
00:03:06,953 --> 00:03:08,422
Why didn't you fight back?

22
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:10,624
Aren't there just four of them?

23
00:03:10,924 --> 00:03:12,325
Based on your skills,

24
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:14,294
you could've taken them down easily.

25
00:03:16,763 --> 00:03:18,365
You're really stupid.

26
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,601
If I fight back,

27
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,805
then I would lose.

28
00:03:28,141 --> 00:03:30,077
I won't be able to protect you.

29
00:03:35,182 --> 00:03:37,084
It's easy to deal with them,

30
00:03:39,953 --> 00:03:41,788
but I had to resist it.

31
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:45,659
I couldn't fight back.

32
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:53,967
I was only thinking about one thing.

33
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,407
And that is to protect you.

34
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:08,482
If I die today,

35
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:12,085
don't be sad.

36
00:04:16,223 --> 00:04:17,824
Don't cry, too.

37
00:04:19,493 --> 00:04:20,727
Daoming Si.

38
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:22,262
Daoming Si.

39
00:04:23,029 --> 00:04:24,898
Daoming Si, don't die!

40
00:04:24,965 --> 00:04:26,566
I don't want you to die!

41
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,235
Daoming Si!

42
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:43,483
Daoming Si.

43
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:44,985
What are you doing over there?

44
00:04:45,051 --> 00:04:46,686
It's too dangerous to stand there.

45
00:04:50,824 --> 00:04:52,292
Can you help me?

46
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:53,794
I can't get up.

47
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:56,596
No.

48
00:04:57,531 --> 00:04:58,765
Stand on your own.

49
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:01,701
Rely on your own strength to go on.

50
00:05:02,769 --> 00:05:03,904
Don't you hate me?

51
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:05,806
Then don't beg me.

52
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:08,175
I hate you?

53
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,343
Who says that I hate you?

54
00:05:11,545 --> 00:05:13,947
Daoming Si, don't do this!

55
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,388
Shancai.

56
00:05:21,454 --> 00:05:23,223
It's great that you're finally awake.

57
00:05:23,290 --> 00:05:25,025
You got me so worried.

58
00:05:25,091 --> 00:05:26,026
Mom.

59
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:27,561
Where are we?

60
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:28,862
We're at the hospital.

61
00:05:28,929 --> 00:05:30,797
You were carried here.

62
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:34,367
You and Daoming Si fainted
at a very remote warehouse.

63
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:36,102
That's right.

64
00:05:36,603 --> 00:05:38,605
Daoming Si lost consciousness.

65
00:05:39,806 --> 00:05:41,474
What exactly happened?

66
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,009
I was so worried.

67
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,378
How do you feel now?
Does it hurt anywhere?

68
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:46,546
Do you feel uncomfortable?

69
00:05:46,613 --> 00:05:47,514
Shancai.

70
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:00,894
Where's Daoming Si?

71
00:06:08,168 --> 00:06:09,636
Is he still alive?

72
00:06:26,152 --> 00:06:27,787
Where is he now?

73
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:41,594
That's impossible.

74
00:07:44,965 --> 00:07:46,299
It's too late.

75
00:07:48,601 --> 00:07:50,170
Ah Si's gone.

76
00:07:57,544 --> 00:07:59,346
Until the very last moment,

77
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:02,916
he was calling your name.

78
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,922
I couldn't believe it.

79
00:08:09,923 --> 00:08:11,958
Ah Si really died just like that.

80
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:43,690
Daoming Si.

81
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,027
Daoming Si.

82
00:08:51,231 --> 00:08:53,133
How can you die?

83
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,002
If you're dead, how can I apologize?

84
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:03,777
Even though you're so stupid

85
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:05,278
and your temper is really bad,

86
00:09:05,912 --> 00:09:08,214
I don't want you to die.

87
00:09:11,451 --> 00:09:13,686
Even though many people want you dead,

88
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:15,989
I...

89
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:19,559
Why are you so noisy?

90
00:09:20,026 --> 00:09:21,628
Is this how you should treat your savior?

91
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:30,603
"I don't want you to die, Daoming Si."

92
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,609
My stomach hurts.

93
00:09:36,676 --> 00:09:37,844
Shancai.

94
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,779
Your facial expression earlier was...

95
00:09:42,115 --> 00:09:43,650
really amazing.

96
00:09:45,618 --> 00:09:48,321
-How infuriating. I want to kill this guy.
-Come back here! Hey!

97
00:09:48,388 --> 00:09:49,956
Do you want to kill me?

98
00:09:50,023 --> 00:09:51,858
My ribs are all broken
and you're even sitting on me.

99
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:53,526
-Are you crazy?
-Who told you to stoop so low?

100
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,328
-It hurts!
-I'm sorry. It's our fault, okay?

101
00:09:55,395 --> 00:09:56,563
-It's all our fault.
-We're sorry.

102
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:57,630
Don't be mad.

103
00:10:01,201 --> 00:10:02,469
-It's so funny.
-Calm down.

104
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:04,938
Not bad, right? Let's go.

105
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:07,574
Have a good rest here.

106
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,042
Leave everything to us.

107
00:10:12,912 --> 00:10:14,948
Lei, wait.

108
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,484
-If you find them, remember--
-All right.

109
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,651
I know what I should do.

110
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:20,086
Get some rest.

111
00:10:29,529 --> 00:10:30,663
Let's have a look.

112
00:10:39,572 --> 00:10:41,441
He wrote down how many punches and kicks

113
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:42,876
he received from each person.

114
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:45,178
I thought he had gotten more mature.

115
00:10:45,245 --> 00:10:48,047
I don't think so. He's still so vengeful.

116
00:10:49,582 --> 00:10:50,416
What's this?

117
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:53,052
"Leave Xiaoshun to me. That's all."

118
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:00,360
Why are you so quiet?

119
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:12,071
What kind of attitude is that?

120
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:13,907
Do you think you're so great?

121
00:11:14,474 --> 00:11:15,775
Why should I be so nosy?

122
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:18,311
I risked my life
and got beaten up so badly

123
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:21,748
just to save an ungrateful virgin.

124
00:11:22,649 --> 00:11:24,717
You're also a virgin.
How dare you say that.

125
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:26,953
Shut up.

126
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:30,924
You always pick fights.

127
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,560
Can't you say nice things
to comfort a patient?

128
00:11:37,664 --> 00:11:38,831
It's because...

129
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:42,368
What is it?

130
00:11:43,603 --> 00:11:45,471
It's because I had a dream.

131
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:47,974
I dreamt that you were dead.

132
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:50,877
I felt so scared.

133
00:11:52,111 --> 00:11:55,949
I wondered if you were really dead.

134
00:11:57,417 --> 00:12:00,220
I thought you wouldn't come and save me

135
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:02,956
after I said those things to you.

136
00:12:04,257 --> 00:12:05,658
I never thought

137
00:12:06,626 --> 00:12:09,462
that you would come
and save me like a stupid fool.

138
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:13,066
You were kicked and hit by those scums.

139
00:12:13,366 --> 00:12:14,901
They beat you up so badly.

140
00:12:15,602 --> 00:12:16,936
You even played a prank of me.

141
00:12:17,003 --> 00:12:19,005
I thought you were really dead.

142
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:25,311
I'm sorry.

143
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,649
Stop rubbing your eyes.
You're already ugly enough.

144
00:12:31,618 --> 00:12:33,620
And haven't I told you before

145
00:12:34,621 --> 00:12:36,389
that even if you go to hell,

146
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,424
I would still go there and pursue you?

147
00:12:39,025 --> 00:12:41,060
Don't struggle pointless anymore.

148
00:12:42,362 --> 00:12:43,563
Stupid fool.

149
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:48,534
What does "struggle pointless" mean?

150
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,436
You meant, "struggle pointlessly," right?

151
00:12:50,503 --> 00:12:51,938
What an idiot.

152
00:12:52,005 --> 00:12:55,441
You always speak Chinese wrongly.
Are you really Chinese?

153
00:12:56,709 --> 00:12:58,945
I think you should study more.

154
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:00,913
What are you laughing at?

155
00:13:01,581 --> 00:13:04,550
I think you had that
pineapple-head hairstyle before

156
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,719
because you're too stupid.

157
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:09,455
That's why all your brain cells
went to your hair.

158
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:12,392
What's the matter?

159
00:13:18,564 --> 00:13:19,565
Xiaoshun.

160
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,301
Haven't you done enough?

161
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:22,568
What else do you want?

162
00:13:23,736 --> 00:13:25,238
Shancai, move.

163
00:13:26,172 --> 00:13:27,140
Why are you here?

164
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:28,174
Don't worry.

165
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:30,777
I'm not here to do anything to you.

166
00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:32,445
Are you here to apologize then?

167
00:13:33,179 --> 00:13:34,113
No way.

168
00:13:35,014 --> 00:13:36,015
Apologize?

169
00:13:36,616 --> 00:13:39,118
I don't think I did you anything wrong.

170
00:13:40,353 --> 00:13:43,056
Compared to the people
you've beaten up in Yingde University,

171
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,692
your wounds are nothing.

172
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:47,994
Yours pale in comparison.

173
00:13:50,897 --> 00:13:53,599
How is that person now?

174
00:13:55,902 --> 00:13:57,303
He transferred to a school in the South.

175
00:13:58,104 --> 00:13:59,339
He's still alive.

176
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:01,474
Are you contented with what you did?

177
00:14:02,275 --> 00:14:03,343
I am.

178
00:14:04,544 --> 00:14:06,479
Even though using Shancai to get to you

179
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:07,914
wasn't an honorable thing to do,

180
00:14:08,881 --> 00:14:11,617
I was able to teach you a lesson
on behalf of those who lived

181
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:13,219
under the shadow of your violence.

182
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:16,289
Even if I'm considered a villain
for doing so, I'm very happy.

183
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:18,224
You can go then.

184
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,892
You've already said
what you wanted to say.

185
00:14:20,993 --> 00:14:22,929
I suggest you stop doing
these things from now on,

186
00:14:23,496 --> 00:14:24,897
for your own good.

187
00:14:25,398 --> 00:14:26,466
Shancai.

188
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:29,235
Actually, I came today
to apologize to you.

189
00:14:30,336 --> 00:14:32,105
I wronged you terribly.

190
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:33,639
Please forgive me.

191
00:14:35,608 --> 00:14:38,511
It's too late to apologize now.

192
00:14:40,079 --> 00:14:41,547
You should leave.

193
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:47,787
Shancai.

194
00:14:48,287 --> 00:14:50,356
If you're not the girl Daoming Si likes,

195
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:54,227
I really hope we could
still be friends someday.

196
00:14:55,695 --> 00:14:57,397
The kind that really
understand each other.

197
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:02,301
I don't think it's possible now, though.

198
00:15:14,046 --> 00:15:15,047
Shancai.

199
00:15:15,548 --> 00:15:16,916
It's really such a pity.

200
00:15:22,655 --> 00:15:23,923
<i>Xiaoshun.</i>

201
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,992
<i>Even though what you did</i>

202
00:15:26,058 --> 00:15:28,027
<i>can be considered as one of the top three</i>

203
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:30,363
<i>most cruel things
I've encountered in my life,</i>

204
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:33,166
<i>Daoming Si also did something wrong.</i>

205
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:36,402
<i>I can actually understand how you feel.</i>

206
00:15:37,003 --> 00:15:38,337
<i>However, at this moment,</i>

207
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:40,106
<i>I really can't forgive you.</i>

208
00:15:43,075 --> 00:15:44,744
That guy is extraordinarily awkward.

209
00:15:46,879 --> 00:15:48,548
I originally wanted to beat him up,

210
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,685
but now, I'm not mad anymore.

211
00:15:53,419 --> 00:15:54,487
Never mind.

212
00:15:57,590 --> 00:15:58,758
<i>Maybe one day,</i>

213
00:15:58,825 --> 00:16:01,093
<i>when time already healed all the wounds,</i>

214
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,929
<i>we can open our hearts together</i>

215
00:16:02,995 --> 00:16:04,430
<i>and be friends again.</i>

216
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:15,274
What do you think? Interesting, right?

217
00:16:15,341 --> 00:16:16,642
Let me see.

218
00:16:18,478 --> 00:16:19,812
This is so exaggerated.

219
00:16:19,879 --> 00:16:21,447
How did they turn out this way?

220
00:16:21,514 --> 00:16:22,815
It only took us ten minutes

221
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:25,384
to handle these guys.

222
00:16:25,952 --> 00:16:27,320
They even cried and yelled for help.

223
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:30,323
They're so lame. They really suck.

224
00:16:30,389 --> 00:16:32,291
Are you sure they were the ones
who beat you up, Ah Si?

225
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:35,127
That's right.
And he got beaten up so badly.

226
00:16:35,194 --> 00:16:36,062
Shancai.

227
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:37,129
You...

228
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:39,799
Ah Si, who has never lost a fight,

229
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:41,300
willingly got beaten up.

230
00:16:41,901 --> 00:16:42,835
That's right.

231
00:16:42,902 --> 00:16:45,271
We initially thought
that he might become a convict

232
00:16:45,338 --> 00:16:46,205
with his personality.

233
00:16:46,806 --> 00:16:48,774
We never thought
that he would do that for you.

234
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:52,411
Though we may not understand it,

235
00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:54,614
the power of love is really great.

236
00:16:56,082 --> 00:16:57,083
I...

237
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,352
I had an examination earlier.

238
00:16:59,819 --> 00:17:01,821
The doctor said I'm fine now.

239
00:17:02,188 --> 00:17:03,723
I'm getting discharged today.

240
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:04,724
Bye.

241
00:17:06,425 --> 00:17:08,828
Don't run away every time
we talk about this, okay?

242
00:17:10,162 --> 00:17:11,898
Ah Si actually has good qualifications.

243
00:17:12,398 --> 00:17:14,667
He has a few hundreds of millions
worth of assets.

244
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:18,204
It's a rare opportunity for you.

245
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:20,473
Consider it carefully, okay?

246
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:22,875
I don't love money that much.

247
00:17:23,910 --> 00:17:24,944
What's so bad about money?

248
00:17:25,011 --> 00:17:26,812
Think about your family, okay?

249
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:29,949
He's also very loyal.
He would never find another girl.

250
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:32,285
He's the best fighter
among the four of us.

251
00:17:32,685 --> 00:17:34,320
That's not considered a good point.

252
00:17:35,154 --> 00:17:37,156
You two should just marry each other.

253
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:39,525
We're already becoming
so impatient watching you guys.

254
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:42,862
Also,

255
00:17:43,696 --> 00:17:45,398
when you're in danger,

256
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:48,868
he will definitely save you
no matter what happens.

257
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:51,370
I didn't ask him to come and save me.

258
00:17:51,938 --> 00:17:53,139
And...

259
00:17:54,173 --> 00:17:55,374
And...

260
00:17:56,042 --> 00:17:57,510
And what?

261
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:02,582
And I think Daoming Si is like a dog.

262
00:18:03,282 --> 00:18:04,350
A dog?

263
00:18:04,717 --> 00:18:06,085
You said I'm like a dog?

264
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,088
<i>I'm such an idiot.</i>

265
00:18:09,155 --> 00:18:11,023
<i>How can I say such a strange thing?</i>

266
00:18:25,972 --> 00:18:27,340
Why are you laughing?

267
00:18:28,007 --> 00:18:29,075
A dog.

268
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:43,623
Knock it off.

269
00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:46,926
He's a male beast
that's full of testosterone.

270
00:18:46,993 --> 00:18:49,028
If he unleashes his savagery,

271
00:18:49,095 --> 00:18:51,797
then I would be in danger.

272
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:57,136
That's not possible.

273
00:18:57,203 --> 00:18:58,938
He also has a lot of good points.

274
00:18:59,505 --> 00:19:00,673
No matter what you say,

275
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:02,308
he's so rich.

276
00:19:02,742 --> 00:19:03,743
Besides,

277
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:05,611
weren't you terribly moved

278
00:19:05,678 --> 00:19:07,013
when he came to save you?

279
00:19:07,713 --> 00:19:09,815
If he doesn't really like you,

280
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:12,985
Daoming Si wouldn't do that.

281
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,163
<i>I really was very moved.</i>

282
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:27,667
<i>Daoming Si, whose pride
is higher than Mount Everest,</i>

283
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:30,136
<i>was humiliated that way because of me.</i>

284
00:19:33,539 --> 00:19:36,809
This has nothing to do with that.

285
00:19:37,977 --> 00:19:40,680
You don't like him,

286
00:19:40,746 --> 00:19:42,048
but you're thinking of dating him.

287
00:19:42,114 --> 00:19:43,849
That's so unconscientious.

288
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:48,487
Do you think I really like Daoming Si?

289
00:19:48,554 --> 00:19:52,458
Does my heart beat fast
like it does with Huaze Lei?

290
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,494
You're so stupid.

291
00:19:56,429 --> 00:19:57,830
If you don't like him,

292
00:19:57,897 --> 00:19:59,465
then just break up with him.

293
00:20:00,266 --> 00:20:01,133
No.

294
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,169
I can't sell myself out that way.

295
00:20:04,637 --> 00:20:06,672
Just think of it as paying him back.

296
00:20:07,273 --> 00:20:08,974
There are many ways to pay him back.

297
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,476
Should I give myself to him as payment?

298
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:11,711
How can I do that?

299
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,918
My head is going to explode.

300
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,621
Ah Si.

301
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:23,789
You're already discharged.

302
00:20:25,257 --> 00:20:26,092
You're here.

303
00:20:30,663 --> 00:20:32,164
Your ribs are connected back together.

304
00:20:32,798 --> 00:20:35,468
Your ability to recover
is like that of a dog.

305
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:38,270
A dog?

306
00:20:38,804 --> 00:20:39,939
Don't mind us.

307
00:20:40,005 --> 00:20:42,408
Shancai must have meant
that you're as cute as a dog, okay?

308
00:20:42,808 --> 00:20:44,610
That's right, that must be it.

309
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:47,413
Stop talking about dogs, okay?

310
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,547
Be careful or I'll kill you.

311
00:20:48,614 --> 00:20:50,816
It seems you received
a serious blow this time.

312
00:20:50,883 --> 00:20:52,218
You won't understand

313
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:54,787
how it feels
when a girl I risked my life to protect

314
00:20:54,854 --> 00:20:55,988
said that I'm like a dog

315
00:20:57,423 --> 00:20:58,724
with that expression.

316
00:20:59,158 --> 00:21:00,593
She said that I'm like a dog.

317
00:21:01,827 --> 00:21:02,895
That stupid girl.

318
00:21:04,463 --> 00:21:05,531
I'm going to bed.

319
00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:06,599
Good night.

320
00:21:09,368 --> 00:21:11,070
Shancai is really stubborn, though.

321
00:21:11,137 --> 00:21:13,739
Girls who emphasize that they're virgins
are especially troublesome

322
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:17,143
because they have a lot of
unrealistic notions about love.

323
00:21:18,344 --> 00:21:19,411
I think so, too.

324
00:21:19,979 --> 00:21:22,681
Or else, she wouldn't like
autistic people like Lei

325
00:21:22,748 --> 00:21:23,816
to such an extent.

326
00:21:26,252 --> 00:21:29,722
Love is that feeling
in that particular moment.

327
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:31,423
That's what makes you feel excited.

328
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:34,293
A feeling in a particular moment?

329
00:21:34,994 --> 00:21:36,195
Is that so?

330
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:41,600
This is between Ah Si and Shancai.

331
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:43,235
Why are you involving me?

332
00:21:45,638 --> 00:21:47,173
Didn't the magazine mention it?

333
00:21:47,606 --> 00:21:50,476
That French guy who proposed to Jing
doesn't seem to have any other plans.

334
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:52,645
What do you plan to do with Jing?

335
00:21:54,513 --> 00:21:55,581
What do you think?

336
00:21:56,882 --> 00:21:58,250
Just wait and see.

337
00:21:58,617 --> 00:21:59,985
God has His own plans.

338
00:22:00,419 --> 00:22:01,620
You're such a strange person, too.

339
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:04,790
When you write the phrase
"in love" in Chinese,

340
00:22:04,857 --> 00:22:06,926
it looks like "change love" instead.

341
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:08,127
I remember now.

342
00:22:08,494 --> 00:22:10,062
In Chinese class
when Daoming Si was younger,

343
00:22:10,129 --> 00:22:11,964
he always writes "in love"
as "change love."

344
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,401
There's nothing we can do now.

345
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:18,571
We can only push that idiot Shancai
to do as we wish bit by bit.

346
00:22:26,879 --> 00:22:27,947
You know,

347
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:30,349
that red card doesn't seem to be from F4.

348
00:22:30,916 --> 00:22:31,917
Then who is it from?

349
00:22:31,984 --> 00:22:34,486
I never thought there would be
such a fearless person in our school.

350
00:22:34,553 --> 00:22:36,121
How would I know?

351
00:22:36,188 --> 00:22:38,891
Anyway, someone dared to use F4's name

352
00:22:38,958 --> 00:22:40,392
to give Shancai a hard time.

353
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:41,927
She deserves it.

354
00:22:41,994 --> 00:22:43,629
She was born with such an unlucky face.

355
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:44,797
She's so annoying.

356
00:22:44,864 --> 00:22:46,866
This proves that we're not
the only ones who hate her.

357
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:48,834
Other people don't like her, too.

358
00:22:48,901 --> 00:22:51,337
-Of course.
-You two are really such nags.

359
00:22:53,105 --> 00:22:54,540
We're chatting among ourselves.

360
00:22:54,607 --> 00:22:55,774
What does it have to do with you?

361
00:22:56,842 --> 00:22:58,377
Who do you think you are?

362
00:22:58,444 --> 00:23:00,846
You want to protect Shancai? Save it.

363
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:03,315
Will you die if you don't talk?

364
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,316
Bigmouths.

365
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:06,518
Who cares, froggy?

366
00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:08,487
Did you call me a frog?
You're the one who's ugly.

367
00:23:08,554 --> 00:23:10,489
You dare to call us ugly?

368
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:11,991
Look at yourself.

369
00:23:12,057 --> 00:23:15,227
You only follow that poor girl Shancai
around all day.

370
00:23:15,294 --> 00:23:19,365
You're an ugly toad
who lusts after a swan.

371
00:23:19,765 --> 00:23:22,167
No, a dried goose.

372
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,235
Let me tell you.

373
00:23:23,302 --> 00:23:24,703
I'm not afraid of you.

374
00:23:25,471 --> 00:23:27,072
A good man doesn't fight with women.

375
00:23:27,473 --> 00:23:29,008
Stop bullying Shancai.

376
00:23:29,475 --> 00:23:31,377
If you don't, I'm warning you.

377
00:23:31,443 --> 00:23:33,212
I won't let it go. I'm scary when I'm mad.

378
00:23:34,380 --> 00:23:36,448
We want you to get mad. Bring it on.

379
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:37,850
Let's go. Come on.

380
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:41,253
I'm so envious of you.

381
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,222
You don't need to see that Shancai

382
00:23:43,289 --> 00:23:44,957
and that big idiot earlier again.

383
00:23:45,024 --> 00:23:45,925
That's right.

384
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:48,360
I'm going to a jewelry appraisal class.

385
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:49,662
How nice.

386
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,864
That means you can shop
to your heart's content

387
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:52,798
in the US.

388
00:23:52,865 --> 00:23:53,933
Of course.

389
00:23:53,999 --> 00:23:56,302
Bring some designer bags
back for me, okay?

390
00:23:56,368 --> 00:23:57,736
That depends on how nice you are to me.

391
00:24:03,709 --> 00:24:04,710
Shancai.

392
00:24:06,145 --> 00:24:07,046
Huaze Lei.

393
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,047
How are you?

394
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:10,082
How are your wounds?

395
00:24:10,916 --> 00:24:11,884
They're all healed.

396
00:24:13,352 --> 00:24:14,820
You've really suffered this time.

397
00:24:17,056 --> 00:24:17,890
How about Daoming Si?

398
00:24:17,957 --> 00:24:20,592
He was discharged last night.

399
00:24:20,659 --> 00:24:21,927
He's on leave today, though.

400
00:24:21,994 --> 00:24:23,762
His wounds haven't completely healed yet.

401
00:24:24,763 --> 00:24:26,565
-He's out of the hospital?
-Yes.

402
00:24:26,632 --> 00:24:28,033
That's great.

403
00:24:30,069 --> 00:24:31,070
Shancai.

404
00:24:33,038 --> 00:24:35,474
Even if we all grew up with him,

405
00:24:35,541 --> 00:24:37,242
this is the first time
we've seen him like this.

406
00:24:38,043 --> 00:24:39,244
We can tell

407
00:24:39,912 --> 00:24:41,347
that he's really serious about you.

408
00:24:42,014 --> 00:24:43,415
You can also tell, right?

409
00:24:43,782 --> 00:24:45,184
Do you know what I mean?

410
00:24:49,788 --> 00:24:50,689
Lei.

411
00:24:51,924 --> 00:24:53,492
You two look quite happy.

412
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:55,794
You're bonding behind my back.

413
00:24:56,228 --> 00:24:57,930
-You two--
-You're so lame.

414
00:24:58,330 --> 00:24:59,965
Aren't you on leave today?

415
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,568
I feel weak from sleeping so much

416
00:25:03,068 --> 00:25:04,236
so I went out.

417
00:25:05,704 --> 00:25:07,539
Your wounds are not
completely healed yet, right?

418
00:25:08,207 --> 00:25:09,475
Why are you moving around so much?

419
00:25:09,975 --> 00:25:12,144
Someone said that my ability
to recover is like that of a dog.

420
00:25:12,745 --> 00:25:15,147
I told you that's just a metaphor.

421
00:25:15,614 --> 00:25:16,782
What an amazing metaphor.

422
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:19,051
Did I ask your opinion, Lei?

423
00:25:20,152 --> 00:25:21,587
All right, I'll go ahead then.

424
00:25:21,987 --> 00:25:23,255
By the way,

425
00:25:23,322 --> 00:25:25,324
I haven't told her what you asked me to.

426
00:25:26,058 --> 00:25:27,192
Just tell her yourself.

427
00:25:27,259 --> 00:25:28,293
I'll go ahead.

428
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,528
-Bye.
-Bye.

429
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:31,296
What is it?

430
00:25:32,998 --> 00:25:34,933
Do you know what day
the 31st of this month is?

431
00:25:37,036 --> 00:25:38,070
No.

432
00:25:38,404 --> 00:25:39,671
You don't know?

433
00:25:39,738 --> 00:25:41,106
It's my birthday.

434
00:25:42,641 --> 00:25:44,343
Happy birthday then.

435
00:25:45,677 --> 00:25:48,113
They always throw a party for me
on that day each year.

436
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:49,915
So, you have to bring a gift.

437
00:25:50,249 --> 00:25:51,183
A gift?

438
00:25:51,250 --> 00:25:53,485
Who asks for a gift themselves?

439
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,287
I also don't have money to buy you a gift.

440
00:25:56,155 --> 00:25:58,424
Stop mentioning money all the time, okay?

441
00:25:58,490 --> 00:25:59,992
But that's a fact.

442
00:26:02,094 --> 00:26:03,629
You can come without a gift then.

443
00:26:03,695 --> 00:26:05,264
Just come.

444
00:26:06,031 --> 00:26:07,733
It's your fault this happened to me.

445
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:09,535
Just treat it like your apology to me.

446
00:26:10,002 --> 00:26:11,637
My mom will be there.

447
00:26:11,703 --> 00:26:13,272
I want to introduce you to her.

448
00:26:13,605 --> 00:26:14,540
Your mom?

449
00:26:15,274 --> 00:26:17,176
My dad can't come because of his work.

450
00:26:17,843 --> 00:26:19,011
Only my mom could come home.

451
00:26:20,712 --> 00:26:22,481
You're introducing me to your mom?

452
00:26:22,548 --> 00:26:23,549
My god.

453
00:26:23,615 --> 00:26:25,951
Daoming Si almost died because of you?

454
00:26:27,119 --> 00:26:28,987
That's like a plot
from a television series.

455
00:26:30,055 --> 00:26:31,590
I'm not made of stone.

456
00:26:31,657 --> 00:26:33,192
Of course, I was moved.

457
00:26:34,026 --> 00:26:37,362
But I'm not really sure
how I feel about Daoming Si.

458
00:26:37,963 --> 00:26:39,965
He always does whatever he wants.

459
00:26:40,032 --> 00:26:41,467
He's so overbearing.

460
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,535
I feel so much pressure because of it.

461
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:47,673
What I'm most worried about now is that
he said he'll introduce me to his mom

462
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:49,942
on his birthday at the end of the month.

463
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:51,243
-Really?
-Yes.

464
00:26:52,244 --> 00:26:53,412
When rich people like them

465
00:26:53,479 --> 00:26:55,180
introduce their girlfriends to their mom,

466
00:26:55,247 --> 00:26:56,315
it must be really formal.

467
00:26:56,815 --> 00:26:58,717
I think it would be
just like an engagement.

468
00:27:01,019 --> 00:27:02,121
"Mother.

469
00:27:02,187 --> 00:27:03,489
This is Miss Shancai,

470
00:27:03,555 --> 00:27:05,424
the girl who I want to spend
the rest of my life with.

471
00:27:06,024 --> 00:27:08,127
-She's nice, right?"
-Xiaoyou, what are you talking about?

472
00:27:08,193 --> 00:27:10,762
We're not even in a relationship.
Spending the rest of our lives together?

473
00:27:10,829 --> 00:27:12,197
You're so cheesy.

474
00:27:12,998 --> 00:27:13,999
Congratulations, Shancai.

475
00:27:14,066 --> 00:27:15,901
You'll become part
of the high society soon.

476
00:27:15,968 --> 00:27:17,903
Cut it out. Stop it.

477
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:20,339
You know it's not what you think.

478
00:27:21,507 --> 00:27:24,343
What I'm most worried about now
is his birthday gift.

479
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:26,478
That's right. The gift.

480
00:27:28,013 --> 00:27:29,248
Have you already prepared it?

481
00:27:30,149 --> 00:27:32,251
I really want to lend you some money,

482
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:34,419
but it's almost the end of the month.

483
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:36,922
I've almost used up the money
I've earned from this job.

484
00:27:37,356 --> 00:27:38,390
Me, too.

485
00:27:38,457 --> 00:27:40,993
There's only 200 bucks left
from my allowance this month.

486
00:27:41,059 --> 00:27:44,630
I really can't go there
empty-handed, though.

487
00:27:47,799 --> 00:27:49,334
You can make it yourself.

488
00:27:49,801 --> 00:27:51,503
It's the thought that counts.

489
00:27:51,570 --> 00:27:53,005
After your shift,

490
00:27:53,071 --> 00:27:55,407
you can bake some biscuits.
What do you think?

491
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:57,342
Biscuits?

492
00:28:04,316 --> 00:28:05,851
I burned them all.

493
00:28:05,918 --> 00:28:07,753
Who wants to eat these?

494
00:28:07,819 --> 00:28:10,355
That's all right. You still have two
to three days before the month ends.

495
00:28:10,422 --> 00:28:11,557
I'm sure you can do it.

496
00:28:13,926 --> 00:28:15,527
It's okay. I can help you.

497
00:28:15,594 --> 00:28:16,595
You can do it.

498
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:21,833
Is it enough?

499
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:23,302
Yes, these should be enough.

500
00:28:30,309 --> 00:28:32,077
Xiaoyou, do you think these look like him?

501
00:28:32,744 --> 00:28:33,879
Yes, they do.

502
00:28:33,946 --> 00:28:34,947
How many did you make?

503
00:28:35,013 --> 00:28:36,315
One, two, three, four...

504
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:37,883
Around five or six pieces.

505
00:28:37,950 --> 00:28:39,851
-If we add these...
-Are they enough?

506
00:28:40,285 --> 00:28:41,119
I'm not sure.

507
00:28:41,186 --> 00:28:42,487
That's okay. I'll help you make more.

508
00:28:42,554 --> 00:28:43,589
Thank you.

509
00:29:01,607 --> 00:29:02,941
Why are you all here?

510
00:29:03,542 --> 00:29:04,710
We came to pick you up.

511
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:07,212
Why are you all dressed that way?

512
00:29:07,813 --> 00:29:10,616
It's the birthday party of Daoming Si,
the heir of the Daoming family.

513
00:29:10,682 --> 00:29:12,251
What are you wearing under that jacket?

514
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:14,586
My mom's dress when she was younger.

515
00:29:16,788 --> 00:29:18,490
Good thing you thought of
picking her up first

516
00:29:18,557 --> 00:29:19,958
or it would've been so embarrassing.

517
00:29:20,993 --> 00:29:22,894
That's right. Come up with a solution.

518
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:24,463
What solution?

519
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:26,431
How would we have time
to get her ready now?

520
00:29:27,666 --> 00:29:28,634
Let's go to Ah Si's house.

521
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:29,534
Why?

522
00:29:29,901 --> 00:29:31,436
Zhuang must have clothes in her room.

523
00:29:35,374 --> 00:29:36,642
What do you want?

524
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:38,377
What are you doing?

525
00:29:39,311 --> 00:29:40,679
Hey, what are you planning to do?

526
00:29:50,856 --> 00:29:53,592
Good thing you thought of using
Zhuang's dresses in her room.

527
00:29:54,226 --> 00:29:55,994
Is it okay to use them
without telling her, though?

528
00:29:56,061 --> 00:29:57,396
It's fine, don't worry.

529
00:29:57,796 --> 00:29:59,231
Zhuang likes Shancai, too.

530
00:29:59,298 --> 00:30:01,366
She knows her mom better than we do.

531
00:30:01,767 --> 00:30:03,802
I think she would understand.

532
00:30:04,703 --> 00:30:07,005
Shancai, what do you think of this one?

533
00:30:07,572 --> 00:30:09,141
Mrs. Daoming
seems to really like this brand.

534
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:10,475
I don't think it suits her.

535
00:30:10,976 --> 00:30:12,978
Shancai would look old in that.

536
00:30:16,214 --> 00:30:17,416
Get your makeup done.

537
00:30:17,949 --> 00:30:19,451
-What do you think of this one?
-Which one?

538
00:30:19,518 --> 00:30:20,419
This one.

539
00:30:21,553 --> 00:30:22,721
I don't think it suits her.

540
00:30:23,622 --> 00:30:24,956
I'm afraid Mrs. Daoming would think

541
00:30:25,023 --> 00:30:27,025
that Shancai is not a decent girl
if she wears that.

542
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:29,828
<i>Why does the atmosphere feel so strange?</i>

543
00:30:29,895 --> 00:30:31,930
<i>Why is Ximen and the others so nervous?</i>

544
00:30:31,997 --> 00:30:33,699
<i>The Mrs. Daoming they're mentioning</i>

545
00:30:33,765 --> 00:30:35,701
<i>is Daoming Si's mom, right?</i>

546
00:30:37,769 --> 00:30:40,472
Hey, I can just wear my own clothes.

547
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:42,107
You don't have to go through
so much trouble.

548
00:30:42,674 --> 00:30:44,543
I think this black cocktail dress
looks nice.

549
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:47,946
Didn't Zhuang had this made
when she was in senior high?

550
00:30:48,380 --> 00:30:49,381
Will it fit Shancai?

551
00:30:49,815 --> 00:30:52,217
Isn't Shancai one size smaller
than Zhuang?

552
00:30:52,818 --> 00:30:54,519
Zhuang had this made
when she was in senior high.

553
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:55,587
It should fit Shancai then.

554
00:30:55,654 --> 00:30:57,222
Excuse me, wait a moment.

555
00:30:58,190 --> 00:30:59,758
Can I ask

556
00:30:59,825 --> 00:31:02,260
why I should dress up so nicely?

557
00:31:02,327 --> 00:31:04,663
Does this birthday party
have any special meaning?

558
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:08,767
We haven't really told you.

559
00:31:09,434 --> 00:31:11,303
Ah Si's mom is a very scary person.

560
00:31:12,037 --> 00:31:12,971
That's right.

561
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,806
She's really hard to get along with.

562
00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:17,309
Especially the way she treats girls.

563
00:31:17,743 --> 00:31:20,212
If she finds out Ah Si
brought you there...

564
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:22,781
Besides,

565
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:25,117
Ah Si is their family's successor.

566
00:31:25,450 --> 00:31:27,052
